    % Draw the diagonal lines to divide the rectangle into triangles
    \draw[pattern=north east lines, pattern color=orange] (0,0) -- (4,4) -- (4,1) -- cycle;
    \draw[pattern=north west lines, pattern color=green] (0,0) -- (4,4) -- (0,4) -- cycle;

    % Label the triangles
    \node at (1,3) {$T_1$};
    \node at (2,2) {$T_2$};
    \node at (3,1) {$T_3$};
    \node at (1,1) {$T_4$};
    \node at (2,0.5) {$H$};

    % Draw the horizontal line at y=b/2
    \draw[thick] (0,2) -- (4,2);

    % Draw the vertical lines
    \draw[thick] (0,0) -- (0,4);
    \draw[thick] (4,0) -- (4,4);

    % Label the sides of the rectangle
    \node at (4.5, 2) {$b$};
    \node at (-0.5, 2) {$\frac{b}{2}$};
    \node at (2, -0.5) {$\partial R$};

    % Draw the horizontal line at y=x
    \draw[thick] (0,1) -- (4,1);

    % Draw the diagonal lines to divide the rectangle into triangles
    \draw[pattern=north east lines, pattern color=orange] (0,0) -- (4,4) -- (4,1) -- cycle;
    \draw[pattern=north west lines, pattern color=green] (0,0) -- (4,4) -- (0,4) -- cycle;

    % Label the triangles
    \node at (1,3) {$\tilde{T}_1$};
    \node at (2,2) {$\tilde{T}_2$};
    \node at (3,1) {$\tilde{T}_3$};
    \node at (1,1) {$\tilde{T}_4$};
    \node at (2,0.5) {$H$};

    % Label the horizontal line at y=x/2
    \draw[thick] (0,0.5) -- (4,0.5);

    % Label the horizontal line at y=x/2
    \node at (2, 0.5) {$x-\frac{b}{2}$};

\end{tikzpicture}

\end{document}
```

This code will produce the two diagrams as described in the caption. The left diagram corresponds to the case \( x \leq \frac{b}{2} \), and the right diagram corresponds to the case \( x > \frac{b}{2} \).

